                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d694">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.248/128: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-31T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 31, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120. Your 163, March 24, 6 p.m. and Department’s 112, March 26, 9 p.m. I am happy
                    to inform you that the President has now released to Greece 30 new Grumman
                    fighter planes under the provisions of the Lend-Lease Act. Some of the planes
                    have already been crated for shipping and the crating of the remainder is
                    proceeding rapidly. Shipping tonnage is understood to have been made available
                    by the British authorities for the immediate transportation of approximately
                    half of these planes to Suez, and arrangements for shipping the remainder have
                    been promised for the relatively near future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
